Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.22,0:00:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A key factor that promotes unity\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.02,0:00:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,among Jehovah’s people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.36,0:00:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is the fact that we receive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.09,0:00:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,very clear direction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.13,0:00:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and regular reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.13,0:00:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think about what we receive each month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.70,0:00:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jehovah’s organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.30,0:00:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfailingly, we receive \Na study edition of The Watchtower; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.34,0:00:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we receive a public edition \Nof The Watchtower or Awake! magazine, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.34,0:00:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the Life and Ministry Meeting Workbook, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.88,0:00:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and an hour-long program \Non JW Broadcasting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.91,0:00:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost daily, we receive new articles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.98,0:00:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,news, and legal updates posted to jw.org. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.99,0:00:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you having a challenge \Nkeeping up with it all? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.46,0:00:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How good to have that button \Non the home page \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.06,0:00:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of jw.org that’s entitled “See What’s New.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.00,0:00:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a gourmet multicoursed meal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.50,0:00:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,these regular provisions \Nfrom Jehovah’s organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.84,0:01:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,not only delight us \Nbut they keep us alive spiritually\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.84,0:01:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—energized to move on \Nin our service to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.61,0:01:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What about those of us \Nwho are entrusted with responsibility, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.38,0:01:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,whether in the congregation \Nor here at Bethel? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.62,0:01:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not lacking for clear direction \Nand regular reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.63,0:01:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You might find it interesting to learn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.96,0:01:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that during the 2016 calendar year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.10,0:01:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,headquarters prepared 80 letters of direction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.60,0:01:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that were sent to the brothers in the field\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.44,0:01:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—such as elders and circuit overseers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.88,0:01:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,For the benefit of the branch committees \Nin 90 branch offices, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.81,0:01:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,during that same time period, \Nthe six Governing Body committees \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.38,0:01:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,sent out 240 letters to help these brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.75,0:01:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,carry out their work in a unified way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.92,0:01:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, that’s in addition \Nto the thousands of letters\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.76,0:01:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that are sent each month in reply \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.20,0:01:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to the individual questions \Nthat come from the branches. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.60,0:01:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Such clear and timely direction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.67,0:02:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is a key factor that contributes \Nto our unity as Jehovah’s people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.61,0:02:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But for a few minutes, \Nlet’s discuss a second factor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.81,0:02:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that strengthens our unity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.81,0:02:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Our commenters all touched on this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.58,0:02:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s our personal willingness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.49,0:02:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to cooperate with theocratic direction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.46,0:02:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In this regard, I invite you \Nto open up your Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.86,0:02:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to Hebrews 13:7. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we’d like to ask the question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.73,0:02:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What type of relationship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,does Jehovah want us to cultivate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.77,0:02:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with our overseers, \Nwith the hardworking elders? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 7 in Hebrews chapter 13 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.78,0:02:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember those \Nwho are taking the lead among you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.35,0:02:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“who have spoken the word of God to you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.48,0:02:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“and as you contemplate \Nhow their conduct turns out, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.89,0:02:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,imitate their faith.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.99,0:02:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s focus \Non the first action word—remember. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.49,0:03:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,To remember means to keep in mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.70,0:03:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the good work an elder does. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.67,0:03:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing so will help us \Nto cultivate warm feelings\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.84,0:03:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,—feelings of love and appreciation \Nfor the elders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.24,0:03:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A recent study edition \Nof The Watchtower says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.84,0:03:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that the word “remember” \Ncould also be translated “mention.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So our heartfelt interest \Nin the elders taking the lead \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.75,0:03:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,moves us to mention them \Nin our prayers to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.76,0:03:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about that relationship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.99,0:03:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that God encourages us \Nto cultivate with our overseers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What a contrast that is \Nto the rebellious, contentious attitude \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.50,0:03:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that many in the world have \Ntoward those in positions of authority.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.47,0:03:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice in this same chapter, \NHebrews chapter 13, what verse 17 adds. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.48,0:03:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re told: “Be obedient \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.88,0:03:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“to those who are taking the lead\Namong you and be submissive, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.32,0:03:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“for they are keeping watch over you \Nas those who will render an account, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.86,0:04:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that they may do this \Nwith joy and not with sighing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for this would be damaging to you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.46,0:04:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we’re admonished \Nto obey and be submissive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.20,0:04:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, obedience is easier \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.81,0:04:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,when we understand the direction given, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when it suits our personal preference. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.34,0:04:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if some theocratic direction \Nwe receive does not make sense, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.75,0:04:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,takes us by surprise, \Nor doesn’t suit us personally? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In such cases, the latter part \Nof that verse comes into play \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.36,0:04:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,where we’re directed to be submissive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.23,0:04:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.16,0:04:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,As the verse highlights, \Nbecause in the long run, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.10,0:04:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,yielding to theocratic direction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.17,0:04:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is for our own good.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.27,0:04:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, this does not make \Nfollowing direction easy\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.38,0:04:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,—knowing that it’s for our good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.68,0:04:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To illustrate the challenge we face, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:05:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you might imagine yourself \Ntrekking in the wilderness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.72,0:05:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Israelites \Nduring that 40-year period. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.02,0:05:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that you and your family \Nhave been walking for some days, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.06,0:05:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden, \Nthe pillar of cloud stops. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.70,0:05:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You stop; you look around; \Nyou’re obedient to the direction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.67,0:05:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But you do ask yourself, \N‘How long will we be here? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.27,0:05:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a day? a week? a few months?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.61,0:05:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask yourself, ‘Should we pack,\Nunpack all of our belongings now?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.61,0:05:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So at the beginning, you decide \Nto unpack just a few things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.45,0:05:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a few days go by, you get tired \Nof hunting through all your belongings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.09,0:05:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so you decide to unpack everything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.22,0:05:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess what happens next? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.23,0:05:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The pillar of cloud \Nstarts lifting up and moving. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.73,0:05:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it’s time to start packing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.30,0:05:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it easy to follow through \Non theocratic direction? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.70,0:05:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not always.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.70,0:05:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In this regard, notice how the Israelites \Nresponded to the movements \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.41,0:06:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah through that cloud. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.45,0:06:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In Numbers chapter 9, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.91,0:06:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,please turn your attention to verse 17, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we’ll read verse 22. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.22,0:06:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Numbers 9:17 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.86,0:06:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whenever the cloud lifted from the tent, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.93,0:06:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“the Israelites would promptly depart, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.30,0:06:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“and in the place \Nwhere the cloud would remain, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.66,0:06:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,there is where the Israelites would encamp.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.87,0:06:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 22: “Whether it was two days, \Na month, or longer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.87,0:06:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“as long as the cloud \Nstayed over the tabernacle, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.01,0:06:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“the Israelites remained encamped \Nand would not depart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.45,0:06:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it lifted, they would depart.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.35,0:06:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you working to cultivate a similar spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.35,0:06:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,toward theocratic direction? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.76,0:06:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bethel family sets \Nan outstanding example in this regard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.76,0:06:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When preparing these comments, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.77,0:07:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t help but think of an overseer \Nthat I worked closely with at Brooklyn Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.67,0:07:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,who always carried in his pocket \Na pen and a notepad. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as someone asked him \Nto follow through on something, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.91,0:07:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out came the pen and notepad \Nand he was making a note. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.25,0:07:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And in many cases\Nbefore the day was over, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,he would have followed through \Non all those action items.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle of Luke 16:10 \Nwas true of this brother: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.79,0:07:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“The person faithful in what is least \Nis faithful also in much.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.80,0:07:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a result, it’s obvious \Nthat Jehovah’s organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.27,0:07:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,has been able to entrust this brother \Nwith many weighty responsibilities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.24,0:07:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that brother is not unique. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.18,0:07:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We have many brothers and sisters \Nin the worldwide brotherhood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.62,0:07:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who demonstrate such an interest \Nin following through \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.22,0:07:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,on theocratic direction.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.39,0:07:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, while visiting \Na branch office in Africa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.76,0:07:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the overseer \Nof the Local Design/Construction Department \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.86,0:08:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,told me that his department meets \Nfor 15 minutes three times a week \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to read out loud a portion \Nof the LDC department guidelines. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.84,0:08:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you like mnemonics, that’s the DC50. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.44,0:08:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he feel that’s necessary? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.28,0:08:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,As he told me, he has found that a review \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.08,0:08:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with the entire department, \Nof the printed direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,helps the whole department to be sure \Nthey’re on the same page\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.99,0:08:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—that they understand the direction clearly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.82,0:08:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The regular review \Nhas also brought to their attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.76,0:08:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,points that they may have overlooked \Nwhen they first read the guidelines \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.26,0:08:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,or that they now understand even better \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.97,0:08:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the light of changing circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.53,0:08:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, another heartwarming example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.10,0:08:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of willing cooperation \Nand prompt follow-through.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.94,0:08:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what does this teach us today? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.25,0:08:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we are being provided \Nwith an abundance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.35,0:08:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of clear direction and timely reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.19,0:09:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is leading us through the elders, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.22,0:09:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,who are taking the lead among us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.26,0:09:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,His presence is as clear to us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.03,0:09:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as it was to the Israelites \Nwho were following \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.56,0:09:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‘the pillar of cloud by day \Nand the pillar of fire by night.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we finish up the final leg \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.97,0:09:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of our wilderness journey, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.17,0:09:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,may we all be resolved to cooperate fully \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.88,0:09:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with any theocratic direction we’re given.\N
